The paper discusses a method for synthesizing probabilistic invariants, which involves finding martingales and applying the optional stopping theorem. This suggests that the paper is likely to be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as well as data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE) since the approach involves analyzing program variables. Additionally, the paper may be related to programming languages (cs.PL) since it discusses finding martingales in probabilistic computations.
